msgid "Summary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Understanding-ROS2-Nodes.rst:181
msgid ""
"A node is a fundamental ROS 2 element that serves a single, modular purpose "
"in a robotics system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Understanding-ROS2-Nodes.rst:183
msgid ""
"In this tutorial, you utilized nodes created from the ``turtlesim`` package "
"by running the executables ``turtlesim_node`` and ``turtle_teleop_key``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Understanding-ROS2-Nodes.rst:185
msgid ""
"You learned how to use ``ros2 node list`` to discover active node names and "
"``ros2 node info`` to introspect on a single node. These tools are vital to "
"understanding the flow of data in a complex, real-world robot system."
msgstr ""

